# Analytics Pipeline System

The Analytics Pipeline is the intelligence backbone of LexMastery.

It turns user behavior into actionable insights.

---

# Product Vision

Analytics must:

- track every meaningful user interaction
- measure learning effectiveness
- power AI personalization
- improve product decisions
- detect user drop-off patterns

---

# Architecture

EventEmitter Layer

↓

AnalyticsController (Riverpod)

↓

Event Queue

↓

AnalyticsProcessor

↓

Remote Analytics Service + Local Cache

---

# Event System

All events must be:

- structured
- typed
- timestamped
- user-scoped

---

# Core Event Categories

## Learning Events
- lesson_started
- lesson_completed
- quiz_attempted
- exam_completed

## AI Events
- ai_query_sent
- ai_response_received
- rag_used
- memory_used

## Engagement Events
- session_started
- session_ended
- streak_updated
- notification_clicked

## Navigation Events
- screen_viewed
- search_used
- feature_opened

---

# Learning Metrics

System must compute:

- completion rate
- retention rate
- accuracy rate
- revision frequency
- mastery progression

---

# Funnel Tracking

Tracks full lifecycle:

- onboarding → first lesson → first quiz → retention → subscription intent

---

# AI Analytics

Tracks:

- response usefulness
- query types
- hallucination risk flags
- RAG dependency rate

---

# Offline Behaviour

- events queued locally
- batch sync when online
- guaranteed delivery strategy

---

# API Contracts

POST /analytics/event

POST /analytics/batch

GET /analytics/summary

---

# State Management

AnalyticsState includes:

- idle
- collecting
- syncing
- failed

---

# Performance Rules

- event logging must be <10ms
- must never block UI
- batch uploads preferred

---

# Data Integrity Rules

- no event loss allowed
- deduplication required
- retry mechanism mandatory

---

# Privacy Rules

- anonymize sensitive data
- allow opt-out
- no raw AI prompt storage unless allowed

---

# UX Rules

- analytics is invisible to user
- only reflected in personalization

---

# Testing Requirements

Unit Tests:

Event validation

Queue system

Batch processing

Integration Tests:

Full analytics pipeline

Offline → online sync flow

---

# Cursor Instructions

When generating analytics features:

- always log structured events
- always batch requests
- never block UI
- always ensure offline persistence